{"key":"post-8626947","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8626947</id>\n<content>Actually, five minutes of direct sunlight while you're right there watching can cause an explosion of pins.&amp;nbsp; Rotate the bin half way through the direct sunlight period to hit the other side of the cakes.&amp;nbsp; It really works.&amp;nbsp; The only danger is drying out, so mist slightly just before the sunlight exposure and fan afterwards.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;As far as times, mushrooms have a circadian rhythm just like us.&amp;nbsp; 12 hours is the standard, but it's great if you just turn it on when you get up, and turn it off after dinner or something.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8626964</next>\n<prev>8626234</prev>\n<first>8625334</first>\n<last>8626964</last>\n<when>1215916699</when>\n<utime>07/13/08 05:38 AM</utime>\n</post>"}